property.description: This full-floor penthouse at Grove at Grand Bay has been conceptualized by Tamara Feldman Design to instill depth and character to this architectural marvel by Bjarke Ingels which twists exotically on the Coconut Grove skyline. Spanning 10,118 square feet of interior space, the proposed design combines various natural elements such as herringbone floors and wood veneer ceilings with cove lighting in the living room and illuminated limestone in the dining room, with oversized bronze doors leading to the office. Under the 12-foot ceilings, the hurricane impact glass walls offer spectacular views of the Coconut Grove waterfront, enveloped by long, deep balconies. Meanwhile, one floor up, an exquisite private roof deck with an oversized pool is your arcadian oasis.
